[679|31950] 18:56:23.746 I/NARR-STATE: narrationState → Speaking(segment=NarrationSegment(id=poi_narration_1530013242063270, text=The Witch House at Salem, located at 310 Essex Street, is a remarkably preserved 17th-century home with a chilling connection to the infamous Salem Witch Trials. Built around 1650, it was the home of Judge Jonathan Corwin, one of the magistrates who presided over the trials in 1692. Today, visitors can tour the house and learn about 17th-century life and the events that unfolded during this dark period in Salem's history., type=LONG_NARRATION, poiName=The Witch House at Salem, voiceId=en-us-x-tpd-local, kind=POI, category=null, refId=poi_narration, isReplay=false)) (autoPlay=true, queueSize=0)
