[1010|31950] 18:57:00.471 I/NARR-STATE: narrationState → Speaking(segment=NarrationSegment(id=poi_narration_1530050446595273, text=The Witch House, purchased by Judge Jonathan Corwin in 1675, is a remarkably preserved example of 17th-century colonial architecture. As a key figure in the Salem Witch Trials, Corwin conducted examinations of accused witches within these walls. Today, the house operates as a museum, offering visitors a glimpse into colonial life and the events surrounding the trials. It remains a powerful and evocative landmark in Salem’s history., type=LONG_NARRATION, poiName=The Witch House, voiceId=en-us-x-tpd-local, kind=POI, category=null, refId=poi_narration, isReplay=false)) (autoPlay=true, queueSize=0)
