[289|7428] 18:59:29.395 I/NARR-STATE: narrationState → Speaking(segment=NarrationSegment(id=poi_narration_1530198656305743, text=Historic Salem, Inc., established in 1944, is a non-profit organization dedicated to the architectural preservation and protection of Salem, Massachusetts.  They publish 'The Salem Handbook,' a valuable resource for understanding the city’s historic dwellings, and collaborated with the Essex Institute in 1983 on 'Architecture in Salem' by Bryant Franklin Tolles.  Historic Salem champions collaborative efforts to safeguard Salem’s historic places while supporting a vibrant future., type=LONG_NARRATION, poiName=Historic Salem, Inc., voiceId=en-us-x-tpd-local, kind=POI, category=null, refId=poi_narration, isReplay=false)) (autoPlay=true, queueSize=1)
