[629|7428] 19:03:52.503 I/NarrationMgr: TTS done: sheet_historic_salem_inc__1530413016615371 (queue remaining: 1)
[630|7428] 19:03:52.504 I/NarrationMgr: playNext: HINT — Historic Salem, Inc. (0 remaining)
[631|7428] 19:03:52.506 I/NARR-STATE: narrationState → Speaking(segment=NarrationSegment(id=sheet_historic_salem_inc__1530413018784833, text=Historic Salem, Inc. has been a vital force in preserving Salem’s architectural heritage since its founding in 1944. Recognizing the importance of protecting the city’s historic buildings and neighborhoods, the organization has worked tirelessly for over eight decades to advocate for responsible development and raise awareness of Salem’s unique character.\n\nPerhaps best known for publishing 'The Salem Handbook' in 1977, Historic Salem provides invaluable guidance to homeowners and enthusiasts interested in the city’s historic dwellings and remodeling projects. This commitment to documentation and education was further demonstrated in 1983 through a collaboration with the Essex Institute to publish 'Architecture in Salem' by Bryant Franklin Tolles, a comprehensive survey of the city’s architectural styles and history.\n\nToday, Historic Salem continues its mission through advocacy, education, and collaborative partnerships, ensuring that Salem’s architectural treasures are preserved for future generations. Their work is essential to maintaining the city’s distinctive identity and celebrating its rich cultural legacy., type=HINT, poiName=Historic Salem, Inc., voiceId=null, kind=POI, category=null, refId=sheet_historic_salem_inc_, isReplay=false)) (autoPlay=true, queueSize=1)
